stories.text:
I'm working on an unusually useful way to leverage a daily journal. I've built a pretty complex system/app, but it uses my personal daily journal, and am at the point where I'd like to demo it to others.

It incorporates some pretty useful features that I haven't seen anywhere else. For my personal journal, I tend to have 5-10 entries per day, so it would be best to showcase a decent volume of data, at least hundreds of entries going back a couple years.

I've search all the usual places and just haven't found something that would work. Ideally it would be from a relatively modern perspective, like within the last 50 years or so, but I guess it could work from older. And for now would prefer something in English and in parsable/plain text format.

Does this ring a bell for anyone?
